  SCIENCE FACTS
============================================================

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   1st Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔU = Q - W
Note:    Energy conservation in thermodynamic systems

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Pythagorean Theorem
Formula: a² + b² = c²
Note:    Right triangle relationship; foundation of geometry

Domain:  Biology
Topic:   Natural Selection
Formula: Favorable traits lead to greater reproduction
Note:    Mechanism of evolution; Darwin 1859

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Euler's Identity
Formula: e^(iπ) + 1 = 0
Note:    Relates five fundamental constants; called most beautiful equation

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Euler's Number
Formula: e ≈ 2.71828182845...
Note:    Base of natural logarithm; fundamental to calculus

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Quadratic Formula
Branch:       Algebra
Formula:      x = (-b ± sqrt(b²-4ac))/2a
Applications: Engineering, physics
Discoverer:   Ancient Babylonians (2000)

Theorem/Law:  Fermat's Last Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      aⁿ + bⁿ ≠ cⁿ for n>2
Applications: Advanced number theory, elliptic curves
Discoverer:   Fermat (conjecture); Wiles (proof) (1637)

Theorem/Law:  Godel's Incompleteness
Branch:       Logic
Formula:      Every consistent system has unprovable true statements
Applications: AI limits, foundations of math
Discoverer:   Kurt Godel (1931)

